candidate.title: Senior Full-Stack Developer
candidate.cv_text:
JANE SMITH
Senior Full-Stack Developer

EMAIL: jane.smith@email.com
PHONE: (555) 123-4567
LOCATION: Melbourne, Australia

PROFESSIONAL SUMMARY
Experienced full-stack developer with 8 years of expertise in building scalable web applications. 
Proficient in modern JavaScript frameworks, Python backends, and cloud architecture. 
Passionate about AI/ML integration and automated testing practices.

TECHNICAL SKILLS
Programming Languages: Python, JavaScript, TypeScript, Java, C#, SQL
Frontend: React, Vue.js, Angular, HTML5, CSS3, Sass, Bootstrap, Tailwind CSS
Backend: Node.js, FastAPI, Django, Express.js, Spring Boot, .NET Core
Databases: PostgreSQL, MongoDB, MySQL, Redis, Elasticsearch
Cloud & DevOps: AWS, Azure, Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, GitHub Actions
AI/ML: TensorFlow, PyTorch, scikit-learn, OpenAI APIs
Testing: Jest, Pytest, Cypress, Selenium
Tools: Git, VS Code, Postman, Jira, Confluence

PROFESSIONAL EXPERIENCE

Senior Full-Stack Developer | Tech Solutions Inc. | 2020 - Present
• Led development of customer-facing web application serving 100k+ users
• Implemented microservices architecture reducing response time by 40%
• Built CI/CD pipeline with automated testing, increasing deployment frequency by 300%
• Mentored junior developers and established code review practices
• Integrated AI-powered chatbot using OpenAI API, improving customer satisfaction by 25%

Full-Stack Developer | Digital Innovations Ltd. | 2017 - 2020
• Developed e-commerce platform handling $2M+ annual revenue
• Built real-time analytics dashboard with React and D3.js
• Optimized database queries reducing load time by 60%
• Collaborated with UX team to improve conversion rate by 35%

Junior Developer | StartupXYZ | 2016 - 2017
• Built responsive web applications using React and Node.js
• Participated in agile development process with daily standups
• Implemented RESTful APIs and integrated third-party services
• Contributed to open-source projects on GitHub

EDUCATION
Bachelor of Computer Science | University of Melbourne | 2012 - 2015
Relevant Coursework: Data Structures, Algorithms, Software Engineering, Database Systems

CERTIFICATIONS
• AWS Solutions Architect Associate (2022)
• Google Cloud Professional Developer (2021)
• Microsoft Azure Developer Associate (2020)

PROJECTS
AI Job Matcher (2023)
• Built full-stack application using React, FastAPI, and PostgreSQL
• Implemented machine learning model for job-candidate matching
• Deployed on AWS with auto-scaling and monitoring

Real-time Chat Application (2022)
• Developed using React, Socket.io, and Node.js
• Supports file sharing, emoji reactions, and group chat
• Handles 1000+ concurrent users

ACHIEVEMENTS
• Top performer award 2021, 2022
• Published article on "Microservices Best Practices" - 10k+ views
• Speaker at Melbourne DevOps Conference 2022
• Contributed to popular open-source project with 5k+ stars

LANGUAGES
• English (Native)
• Mandarin (Conversational)
• Spanish (Basic)
